'''Blackridge''' is a community in eastern [[Allegheny County, Pennsylvania|Allegheny County]] and is a suburb of [[Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania]]. This community consists of about 650 private homes built from 1920 to 1949. Blackridge Estates was and remains one of the area's largest residential communities.

Blackridge lies in the municipalities of [[Wilkinsburg, Pennsylvania|Wilkinsburg]], [[Penn Hills, Pennsylvania|Penn Hills]] and [[Churchill, Pennsylvania|Churchill]]. It maintains a Civic Association and a private park and swim club for residents.

Blackridge is defined<ref name="blackridge-area">{{cite web | url = http://www.blackridge-bca.org/membership/membership.asp | title = Welcome to the Blackridge Civic Association | publisher = Blackridge Civic Association | date = 2011-08-26 | accessdate = 2011-08-26 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110806053756/http://www.blackridge-bca.org/membership/membership.asp | archive-date = 2011-08-06 | url-status = dead }}</ref> as the territory bounded on the West by Graham Boulevard, on the South by William Penn Highway, on the East by Beulah Road and the Churchill Country Club property, from the Churchill Country Club property along Orlando Place to Atkinson Place, Atkinson Place to Pine Way, and Pine Way to Graham Boulevard, and includes the properties fronting on both sides of said portions of Country Club Drive, Orlando Place, Atkinson Place and Pine Way.

The [[Pittsburgh History and Landmarks Foundation]] Historic Landmark "[[List of Pittsburgh History and Landmarks Foundation Historic Landmarks|1939 House]]" (''[[Good Housekeeping]]'' house) is located in Blackridge at 2363 Sebring Place in the Wilkinsburg section of the neighborhood.

